<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idca390b65-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s1473d"><num value="1473d">§ 1473d.</num><heading> Insurance costs covering vehicles, aircraft, and boats operated by Department of the Interior in Canada and Mexico</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Notwithstanding any other provisions of law, in fiscal year 1992 and thereafter, appropriations in this title <ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002094">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002094"><num>1</num> See References in Text note below.</note> shall be available to provide insurance on official motor vehicles, aircraft, and boats operated by the Department of the Interior in Canada and Mexico.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idca390b66-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/pl/102/154/tI/s107">Pub. L. 102–154, title I, § 107</ref>, <date date="1991-11-13">Nov. 13, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/1012">105 Stat. 1012</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idca390b67-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idca390b68-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idca390b69-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">This title, referred to in text, is title I of <ref href="/us/pl/102/154">Pub. L. 102–154</ref>, <date date="1991-11-13">Nov. 13, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/990">105 Stat. 990</ref>, known as the Department of the Interior and Related Agencies Appropriations Act, 1992. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Tables.</p>
</note>
